        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "test(qa): add mapped qa run profiles",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds `pnpm openclaw qa run --profile smoke-ci|release` as the mapped QA profile entry point on top of the taxonomy mapping evidence map.\n- Resolves profile/surface/category selectors to mapped scenario refs, converts them to QA suite scenario IDs, and dispatches through the existing `qa suite` runner.\n- Preserves existing `qa run` self-check behavior when no mapped QA profile is provided, and preserves old root-profile parsing for non-mapped `qa run --profile <name>` values.\n- Updates the public QA overview with mapped profile examples and adds `qa/AGENTS.md` plus the required `qa/CLAUDE.md` symlink for agent-ready QA mapping guidance.\n\nStacked on #91500.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/cli.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/cli.runtime.test.ts src/cli/profile.test.ts`\n- `pnpm openclaw qa run --profile smoke-ci --category agent-runtime-and-provider-execution.agent-turn-execution --provider-mode mock-openai --output-dir .artifacts/qa-e2e/smoke-ci-profile-dispatch --allow-failures`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `pnpm format:docs:check`\n- `git diff --check origin/dallin/coverage-taxonomy-validation...HEAD`\n- `git diff --check`\n- live PR diff/body check for personal-name owner references\n",
